	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=121686><span id=Scholar>Noirac</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>17 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.06]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Yes charm kitting is good but always better if you avoid hits!!! :)<br>You dont have to stay and wait for mobs to hit you...just charm 1 mob then facing your train hit F8 (this will target the nearest monster, your pet is not considered as a monster now) and create a Hotkey /pet attack.<br>So here is what to do:<br>_Make a train<br>_charm 1 mob<br>_face your train<br>_hit F8<br>_hit your hotkey /pet attack<br>_!!!press 2 times F1!!!! &lt;= this will target your pet again!!!!<br>_charm your pet again<br>_and continue :)<br><br>The tip is to find your pet in so many looking like mobs : Press 2 times F1 (first you then your pet!)<br><br>Good luck I hope it help<br><br>Valaba<br>55 Bard<br>Therris Thulle<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue May 21 12:52:34 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
