	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=4&mid=10213920989995>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=10213920989995>Fear Kiting in a dungeon</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=10213920989995#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, May 14th 12:10 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=45258><span id= >FrenchWrath</span></a><br><span id=notbold>2 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Well, here is how I did it in lower guk live side and Sol B on Sol A side:<br>1) go down the ramp and try to pull a single mob with chain (use lull if necessary).<br>2) run back all the way to the zone (can be quite a run) and wait for the mobs<br>3) if more than one mob comes, you have two options:<br>- charm one of them and attack the other... This will prevent you from fear kiting as you can't twist songs while charming a mob and fighting another.<br>- you decide you don't care about adds which might be just as good.<br>4) at this point, start twisting Jonathon's, chain and fear (and a 4th one of your choice (regen is a good choice with multiple mobs)). The extra mobs will start running away and you will be able to focus one that one mob you snared.<br>5a) now if you had pulled more than one mob, go back up the ramp as soon as your fear breaks and start over<br>5b) if you managed to do a single pull, just keep twisting these songs until you reach a point where you might start a train if you go further. At that point, break from the fight and go back to zone. When the mob comes back, repeat as necessary.<br>This worked really great for me (better in lguk than solB where mobs tend to hit hard and resist more) but:<br>- I had my brass skill maxed (just let your computer run on a fear song while going to work to max it out)<br>- I had a good AC although my HPs are really not that great.<br>I managed to do a little over a yellow bub per hour in there. Later on, I grouped with a wizzie friend and I used the same technique. Just tell him to assist you and nuke once and wait for next mob etc...<br>good luck and let me know if you find other areas like this for higher levels...<br>Hayna Miaoumix, Xegony</p>