	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61546><span id=Sage>Slipskin</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>1056 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.25]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>BA armor is not bad at that level.&nbsp;&nbsp;You might consider trying Fine Steel Plate.  Looks really cool on Vah Shir. Kind of a brushed gun metal gray color without dye. Better AC than BA, too. Almost as good as Lambent. Not as expensive as Lambent. It is heavier than Lambent.<br><br>For a weapon consider a polished granite tomahawk for use while soloing.  It procs a 20 HP damage absorbtion + STR buff that is good until you get to level 30 or so.<br><br>The combine drum from Katta is around 87pp and is a bit better than the regular drum. Same with the combine lute (about 50pp).  But, you could probably buy a set of Mistmoore Drums for 500-1000p (not sure of going rate on all servers).<br><br>The DEX /AGI ring is nice but you might want to trade it for a DEX/CHA jewelry instead.  If you plan to solo some higher level bards in my guild recommend CHA and HP stuff.  Soon you will be able to charm kite.  High CHA helps a lot there.<br><br>Check out EQDiva.com.  Best EQ bard site I have seen.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu May  9 09:26:50 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222</a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760</a></td></td></tr>
