	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=4&mid=102027407164012>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=102027407164012>RE: Equipment</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=102027407164012#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, May 1st 1:27 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=113466><span id=Sage>rutkoskyd</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>62 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.46]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;I personally would go for the Lambent Boots because of the additional AC and the saves.  The +1 cha helps with charming and mezzing, as well.  I like the str and dex stats of the Dwarven Work Boots but I wouldn't sacrifice the AC.  This, of course, is a decision based on the role I choose to play.  The versatility of the bard allows him/her to play in many different roles and the equipment you choose should reflect that.  I'm very much AC dependent because I tend to find myself filling the role of secondary tank (and on some VERY rare occasions primary).  The str and dex boosts would be nice for a manabattery bard that occasionally steps in for a hit or two--it'd make those few hits count!  Enjoy your bard for you are one of the few classes that can tank, heal, be a manabattery, and even run crowd control.  Develop your gear to mirror the role you find yourself in the most, but don't become too one-sided--you may be called upon to fill one of the other roles.<br><br>   High end instruments are worth every cp.  Let's take the Mistmoore Battle Drums as a quick example.  These aren't selling for 5k, but provide a nice analogy.  They lack stats, but will make most of your songs 23% more effective than played with a standard, store bought hand drum.  This translates to more powerful DOT chants, a faster run song, and more.  Instrument upgrades are wise investments so don't shy away from spending a pretty penny on that Walrus Skin Drum :P  Enjoy.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed May  1 13:28:52 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
